com.googlecode.transmuter.type
Class TypeToken.ValueType<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.googlecode.transmuter.type.TypeToken.ValueType<T>
Type Parameters:
T - a wrapper type or Void.
Enclosing class:
TypeToken<T>
public abstract static class TypeToken.ValueType<T>
extends Object

An enum-like class which represents Java's primitive data types (plus void). Each instance of this class holds two type tokens: one with a primitive type and the other with the matching wrapper type.

It behaves logically like an enum, except that Java enums don't take generic parameters.
